@startuml
' Set theme for better readability
'!theme plain

' You can set a global background color for all notes if you want
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #Yellow


' Define a title for the diagram
title Flutter ScrollView Class Hierarchy

' --- Define Classes ---
' Using "abstract" keyword for abstract classes
abstract class Widget
abstract class StatelessWidget
abstract class ScrollView
abstract class BoxScrollView

class CustomScrollView
class ListView
class GridView
class PageView

' --- Define Inheritance Relationships ---
' Using "<|--" for inheritance (Child <|-- Parent)
StatelessWidget <|-- ScrollView
StatelessWidget <|-- PageView
Widget <|-- StatelessWidget

ScrollView <|-- CustomScrollView
ScrollView <|-- BoxScrollView

BoxScrollView <|-- ListView
BoxScrollView <|-- GridView

' --- Add Notes for Variation/Factory Constructors ---
' These aren't separate classes, so notes are the best way to represent them.
note top of ScrollView
 <b>All scrollables intentionally passes
 <b>unconstrained (or unbounded) maximum
 <b>dimension constraints to its child
 <b>along the scroll direction (the main axis).

 All core scrollable widgets in
 Flutter follow the same rule as
 <b>SingleChildScrollView</b>: they give
 their content infinite space in the
 direction of the scroll. This is necessary
 so the content can size itself to its
 natural, potentially oversized, dimensions.
end note

note left of ScrollView
 <b><u>In the Scroll Direction (Main Axis)
 ===Constraint Passed: minSize = 0.0, maxSize = ∞

 <b>Result</b>: The child is given an infinite maximum
 space. This allows the child widget (e.g., a
 <b>Column</b> or <b>Container</b> to report a size
 that is as large as its total content requires,
 even if it exceeds the screen size.

 <b>Key Consequence:
 You cannot use widgets like <b>Expanded</b> or
 <b>Flexible</b> directly inside a <b>Column</b> or <b>Row</b> that
 is the child of a scrollable (along the scroll direction).
 Since the available space is infinite, the <b>Expanded</b>
 or <b>Flexible</b> would try to take an infinite size,
 leading to an error.
end note

note bottom of ListView
  <b>Variations (constructors):</b>
  - ListView.builder
  - ListView.separated
  - ListView.custom

  has children
end note

note bottom of GridView
  <b>Variations (constructors):</b>
  - GridView.builder
  - GridView.count
  - GridView.extent
  - GridView.custom

  has children
end note

note bottom of CustomScrollView
  has slivers
end note

' --- Grouping with Packages (Optional but good for clarity) ---
'package "Base Abstract Classes" {
'  class ScrollView
'  class BoxScrollView
'}

'package "Specific Layout Implementations" {
'  class CustomScrollView
'  class ListView
'  class GridView
'}

' Hide empty members for a cleaner look
hide empty members

@enduml